  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed comprehensively across all model inputs, propagating boundary condition variability, fluid property uncertainty, and hemolysis power-law coefficient distributions through the full CFD pipeline. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
