      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QOI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on fine mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (6.2M, 14.8M, 31.4M cells). Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 3.1% for the normalized index of hemolysis on the fine mesh. Discretization error is within the accepted threshold."
