      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, hematocrit) are documented with calibrated instrumentation and traceable uncertainty budgets.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments conducted with bovine blood at 37 °C, hematocrit 33±2%, flow rates measured by calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5%). All five operating points are fully documented with NIST-traceable calibration records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty Uval) reported for hemolysis index at all five operating points; comparison norm accounts for experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis predictions agree with experimental measurements within combined validation uncertainty (Uval) at all five operating points. Mean absolute error is 8.3% across the operating envelope, within the acceptance threshold of 15%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
