      "rationale": "Simulation setup was peer-reviewed by a second CFD engineer. One operating point was independently replicated, yielding hemolysis index within 1.2% of primary analyst result. Use error controls are adequate."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparative study; hemolysis power-law model form validated against benchmark datasets; model form uncertainty estimated.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected following comparison with RSM and k-epsilon on the FDA pump; SST yields lowest hemolysis prediction error. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model validated against Heuser-Opitz dataset. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% of predicted hemolysis index."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed across full input space; output uncertainty intervals reported at 95% confidence.",
      "rationale": "Comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all model inputs, including inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis power-law coefficients. Ten thousand Monte Carlo samples were propagated through the surrogate-assisted CFD pipeline. Ninety-five percent confidence intervals for the normalized index of hemolysis are reported at all five operating points. All input distributions are grounded in experimental characterization data."
    },
